@hm just has a campaign out, with beautiful pictures taken in Brasil, soundtrack you can hear with Brasilian music, but oh the irony: HM is using cotton from areas that should be preserved ( is HM aware of the massive floodings in south Brasil right now?) This is from april 19 th. : A year-long Earthsight investigation found that fiber certified by ethical supply chain organization Better Cotton was grown on â€œstolenâ€ and â€œdeforestedâ€ land in Brazil. A year-long investigation by nonprofit Earthsight published last week found that cotton grown on what the group said is â€œstolenâ€ and â€œdeforestedâ€ land in Brazilâ€™s Cerrado region appeared in garments approved by supply chain certifier Better Cotton and sold by retail giants H&M and Zara parent company Inditex.
The traced cotton is grown in the Brazilian state of Bahia by two of the countryâ€™s largest producers, SLC AgrÃ­cola and Grupo Horita, per the report, which said both companies have been fined repeatedly for environmental violations. The investigation traced the cotton to eight Asia-based clothing manufacturers that supply H&M and Inditex with â€œmillionsâ€ of garments, per the investigation. So it is absolutely provoking that HM ignores that and still use the Brasilian florests to shoot their campaign, like they care..
